$interpreted: Rune: Valdrir...!
Sophie: Rune!
Rune: ...Sophie...
Eidatyr: Val?!
Eidatyr: You're making the sacrifice all by yourself... You idiot!!
Eidatyr: Dammit... Goddammit...! Come out of there, Val! Valdrir!!
Sophie: Don't go, Rune, it's too dangerous!
Rune: I go, help her.
Sophie: No! You'll die if you set foot in there!
Hanbei: Yup, Eidatyr was telling us all about it the whole way here. How twins born to the clan would be engraved with a matching pair of runes—
Eidatyr: A pair of twins... One to absorb life, another to release it.
Eidatyr: The Grand Sorcerer holds a ritual to set the twins' cycle in motion, gathering up all the Soul Energy of the surroundings to open up the volcano.
Eidatyr: ...But this energy is tremendous, overwhelming.
Eidatyr: In previous sacrifices, the twins gave every drop of their life force to the ritual and died before the volcano could be unsealed.
Eidatyr: And I'm afraid that this time...
Sophie: Do you see, Rune? It's hopeless!
Rune: No. Can't leave. Valdrir.
Sophie: Rune... Come back!
Rune: Valdrir, is family. Can't leave, to die.
Sophie: ......
Sophie: (I'm sorry...)
Sophie: Rune! I'm ordering you to go back with us.
Rune: ...Huh?
Sophie: ...Did you hear me, Rune?
Rune: Sophie, ordering?
Sophie: Yes, I'm ordering you...
Rune: ...Why... even Sophie, you...
Sophie: I'm sorry, I know it's selfish, but... you're too important to me...
Rune: ...Don't cry.
Rune: Sophie, important to me, too. Sophie smiles, so pretty.
Rune: I love, Sophie.
Sophie: Rune...
Rune: Lots of things, don't understand. I'm stupid. But, I don't want, make Sophie cry. I'll go, figure it out.
Rune: ...Then, I give, my own orders.
Valdrir: Rune?! What are you...
Rune: I never, told you. You, I don't understand.
Rune: I want, understand you, Sister. Family.
Valdrir: ......
Valdrir: ...I'm sorry... I should have been protecting you...
Rune: I support you, to the end. We survive, together.
Valdrir: ...Yes. We'll talk, and understand, when the time comes.
Valdrir: *sob*...
Rune: Guh...!
Gretta: (They're not children anymore, perhaps they've grown far apart... They're so much less alike than in previous rituals...)
Gretta: (Please, you have to live...)
Valdrir: ...Urgh...
Rune: ...Grgh...
Sophie: What should we do? They can't hold on much longer!
Eidatyr: This $%*&ing volcano better hurry up!
Ru-yi: Look! It's opening!
Hutchinson: Monsters!
Eidatyr: $@%#&! Stop those evil villains!
Sophie: Urgh, I... I can't go on...
Eidatyr: Bwahaha... So it didn't open at all. I guess this is the end for all of us, then...!
Dylan: Heroic Soldiers of the Sun! The Kingdom is facing a grave crisis. I swear to give my life to rescue our Queen!
Sun Soldier: For the Queen!
Dylan: Charge!!
Naya: Urgh... guh... Angelia... Go now...
Angelia: Wake up, Naya... Please, wake up...
Naya: Angelia... Don't worry... I'll always... keep you safe...
Angelia: Naya... Naya...!
Zola: —Your friend here's not getting any better~
Zola: Good news, Carlos~ Today's seen a lot of casualties~
Angelia: ...What do you mean...
Zola: Your rescue team have just been beaten back. Between them and the Twelve Nobles' forces, it's a total bloodbath out there.
Zola: Just think, all those loyal Carlos supporters, heheheh...
Angelia: Oh...!
Naya: Ungh...!
Angelia: Naya?! Naya! Wake up! Don't leave me, Naya!
Zola: Yes, Carlos, more pain, more tears! Wonderful! Ahaha...
Angelia: Enough! I'll do what you want of me! Just save Naya, save her!
